[T0] [tier:2] Migrated Archaiforge from CLI-era v6.5.0-beta to Desktop MCP (desktop-1.0). Archived legacy structures (context/, extensions/, heartbeat/, reflex/, vectors/, START_HERE.md, boundaries.yaml) into .archaiforge/archive/pre-desktop-2026-01/. Removed obsolete protocol relay files (.clinerules, .cursorrules, .windsurfrules). Updated config.json with new version, desktop_mcp mode, and full migration history. The .amem manifold (49KB) was preserved as-is — it is the modern structure. Three historical backups retained.
[T0] [tier:2] [ARCHITECTURE] Bags & Brats is a church cornhole tournament management system. Stack: Flask (Python 3.11) + React (Vite) + MongoDB + Docker Compose. Real-time via Socket.IO + Eventlet. Auth: JWT (flask-jwt-extended) with Google OAuth + Apple Sign In + email/password. Deployed to Railway (backend: bagsbrats-production.up.railway.app, frontend: efficient-insight-production.up.railway.app). Backend uses Flask app factory pattern with blueprints (main routes + oauth). Frontend uses React Router v6 with PrivateRoute guard. Design system: Outfit font, teal brand (#5dc6cf), glassmorphism cards, dark/light theme toggle, Framer Motion animations. Lucide icons throughout.
[T0] [tier:2] [DATA MODEL] Four MongoDB collections: users (name, email, phone, password_hash, google_id, apple_id, role=player|admin, is_proxy, checked_in, checked_in_at, is_power_player, power_player_used, has_paid), tournaments (name, dates[], status=upcoming|active|blackout, current_day_index, current_round, rounds_per_day, start_times[], check_in_open), games (tournament_id, date, game_number, court, team1_player_ids[], team2_player_ids[], score1, score2, status=upcoming|active|finalized, start_time, end_time, submitted_by, is_power_game, day_index, round_number), teams (tournament_id, day_index, player_ids[], is_power_team, team_number). Teams are PERSISTENT per day — same teams play all rounds.
[T0] [tier:2] [TOURNAMENT ENGINE] Core pairing algorithm in backend/app/utils.py. Uses modular arithmetic on checked-in player count (n%4) to determine normal (2v2) vs power (1v2) game distribution. Power Players are opt-in volunteers who solo against pairs when player count is not divisible by 4. The system tracks power_player_used to rotate who solos. Teams persist for the entire day — Round 1 creates teams, subsequent rounds reuse them with different matchups. Anti-repeat logic prevents same teams from facing each other twice in a day. Tournament lifecycle: upcoming→active→blackout (hides standings)→finalized. Multi-day support with day_index tracking. Rounds managed per-day (default 3). Check-in window opens at configurable hour (default 5pm America/Chicago) or admin can manually open. APScheduler runs midnight reset of checked_in and has_paid flags.
[T0] [tier:2] [REAL-TIME & UX] Socket.IO events: pairings_revealed (broadcasts new game pairings to tournament room), blackout_status (hides/shows standings), standings_updated (triggers client refresh). Frontend Socket service in frontend/src/services/socket.js. Player Dashboard is a state machine: no_tournament→waiting→active (playing game with 20min countdown timer)→between_rounds (shows completed game results)→day_complete (awaiting Big Reveal). Score submission by any team participant finalizes the game. Admin controls: generate pairings, start/stop rounds, toggle check-in, toggle blackout, Big Reveal launch. Big Reveal is a dramatic sequential podium: 3rd→2nd→1st (Golden Bag Winner) with Framer Motion spring animations and confetti overlay. Power Player toast appears after 12s on player dashboard for non-power-players as a recruitment mechanism.
[T0] [tier:2] [API SURFACE] Backend routes (backend/app/routes.py, 1109 lines). Auth: POST /auth/register, POST /auth/login, GET /auth/me. Player: POST /player/check-in, GET /player/current-game, GET /player/day-summary. User profile: PUT /user/profile, PUT /user/password, PUT /user/power-player. Admin user mgmt: GET /admin/users, POST /admin/users/<id>/role, PUT /admin/users/<id>, DELETE /admin/users/<id>, PUT /admin/users/<id>/reset-password, POST /admin/users/<id>/toggle-paid, POST /admin/users/<id>/check-in, DELETE /admin/users/bulk-delete, POST /admin/users/seed. Tournament: POST /tournaments, GET /tournaments/active, GET /tournaments/standings, DELETE /admin/tournaments/bulk-delete. Game: POST /games/<id>/submit, POST /games/<id>/start, GET /tournaments/active/games. Admin game: POST /admin/generate-pairings, POST /admin/round/start, POST /admin/round/stop, GET /admin/round/status, POST /admin/tournament/start-all, POST /admin/tournament/stop-all, POST /admin/tournament/blackout, POST /admin/tournament/toggle-checkin, GET /admin/tournament/top-teams, GET /admin/games, POST /admin/games/<id>. OAuth: GET /auth/google, GET /auth/google/callback, GET /auth/apple, POST /auth/apple/callback. Admin proxy: POST /admin/proxy-register.
[T0] [tier:2] [FRONTEND PAGES & COMPONENTS] 8 pages: Login (email/password + Google/Apple OAuth buttons), Register (name/email/phone/password form), OAuthCallback (token extraction from redirect), PlayerDashboard (check-in, game view with countdown timer, score submission, personal stats, Power Player toast), AdminDashboard (4 tabs: Controls/Overview/Roster/Games with tournament creation calendar, RoundManager, Big Reveal launch, proxy registration), UserSettings (profile editing, password change, Power Player opt-in), BigReveal (sequential podium reveal with animations), SpectatorView (public standings). 7 components: AdminGameManagement, AdminProxyRegister, AdminUserManagement, PrivateRoute (JWT guard with requireAdmin prop), RoundManager (per-round generate/start/stop), ThemeToggle (dark/light), TournamentStandings. All styling via CSS variables in index.css — glassmorphism cards, teal brand, Outfit font.
